Arabic Language
•Language of the Quran
•One of the most widely spoken languages in the world
•300+ Million Speakers
•Official Language in 22 countries
Link: Sample Arabic Calligraphy
•28 Alphabets ()
•3 Vowel Sounds ()
•Three letter root system
•No neutral gender
•Conjugated for Singular, Dual & Plural
•Strong Morphology ()
•Systematic Grammatical Rules ()
Study of Arabic language can be grouped into two main branches:

 and 
• deals with the rules concerning formation of a word
•deals with the grammatical rules concerning formation of phrase or
sentence.
•There is another branch () which the science of rhetoric.
